JD - 11 :

What You Will Be Responsible For :  As Global Delivery Operations CAO – Vice President you will
- Ability to partner with multiple seniors and stakeholders effectively to drive the GD India strategy forward.
- Drive and assist to successfully plan, manage, and execute the priorities and a variety of initiatives defined for the business unit.
- Proficient in independently translating a vision into impactful presentations with mastery of both written and oral communication.
- Overcomes obstacles by self-identifying alternatives, developing useful multiple alternative solutions concurrently, and converging on a selected alternative once obstacle has been cleared.
- Ability to demonstrate strategic mindset by analyzing data and presenting it a manner that satisfies needs of stakeholders across all levels of the organization including senior management.
- Ability to create executive-level presentations with experienced in written communications for executive reviews.
- Adept at negotiating and handling difficult situations effectively.
- Must be analytical in problem-solving and decision-making and be comfortable in defining and implementing data driven decision-making processes.
- Coordinate completion of functional reporting; Including preparing materials with key metrics and insights
- Track YTD headcount, budget, attrition and reporting on potential challenges of Hiring /resources
- OKRs tracking and updates and support with driving governance for the organization.

What We Value

These skills will help you succeed in this role
- Strong analytical background, with a keen inclination to solve problems. Strong MS Office skills (PowerPoint, Word, Excel, tableau, SharePoint)
- Excellent communications skills, written and verbal and great presentation skills.
- Executive presence, managing with influence and effective communication across stakeholder groups both regionally and globally
- Ability to focus on multiple, time-sensitive activities without compromising the quality of work.
- Highly proactive person who demonstrates initiative and ownership and can work with little direction on complicated, sensitive assignments.
- Experience working in a global environment and with organizational change.
- Embed risk excellence culture across the teams & encourage and drive a culture of change and ideation


Education & Preferred Qualifications

- Bachelor’s degree and an advanced degree in Business Administration or other related field
- Possess excellent communications skills with evidence of successful leadership and administrative/supervisory experience
- 12 plus years of experience in a COO / CAO role across the banking industry
- Highly skilled in Power point and other prominent Microsoft offerings.
- Proven ability to analyze trends, encourage and make recommendations for creative change
- Results-oriented individual with the persistence and patience necessary to work effectively with a wide range of internal and external constituents
- Demonstrated ability to partner with senior level staff, middle management and administrative divisions.
- Proven ability to handle multiple priorities and lead team efforts
Strong numerical ability, analytical, interpersonal, written, and oral presentations skills
Attention to detail and a flair for numbers
Demonstrate skills in problem assessment and resolution as well as collaborative problem solving in a complex setting required

